Membership Landing
Join Our Club
Membership
Having celebrated our 55th anniversary in 2021, The Country Club of Naples is one of Naples most established private, full-service country clubs.  CCN Members enjoy an exceptional golf course which was completely renovated in 2023, and a wonderful clubhouse (renovated in 2016) with multiple outdoor dining options.  The Club has one of the area's newest golf courses with an exciting year-round social calendar.
We invite you to inquire - Membership Landing
We invite you to inquire about our Golf Memberships and explore all that CCN has to offer. Please contact Kristen Yanzer, our Membership Director at
239-919-8021
or
[email protected]
.

Weddings & Private Events
Weddings & Private Events
The ideal location for your special event
The Country Club of Naples' convenient location in the heart of Naples is the perfect venue to host your special event, wedding or banquet.
*
Our completely renovated clubhouse opened in November, 2016. Inspired by a classic Old Florida feel, the new clubhouse provides a warm and welcoming experience for you and your guests.
The Club offers a variety of special event rooms with beautiful views of the golf course. The Ballroom can accommodate up to 230 guests, as well as be divided up to accommodate a smaller event.
Features of The Country Club of Naples:
Outstanding in-house culinary team and service staff
A variety of lunch and dinner menus
State-of- the-art wireless technology to provide whatever your group may need in the way of AV equipment, microphones, screens, etc.
We invite your inquiry.  It would be our pleasure to help make your event a memorable one.  For additional information, please contact our Club Events Manager, Ixel Swanson at
239-261-1032
ext 4 or by email at
[email protected]
*Note:  As a private club, all non-member functions must be sponsored by a member.

Proud Heritage... Bright Future - Abous Us Landing
Proud Heritage... Bright Future
where members become friends
Proud Heritage... Bright Future
The Country Club of Naples is a member-owned Club with a proud heritage dating back to 1966. Centrally located off Goodlette and Solana Roads, CCN just minutes from your neighborhood. We are not a gated community and there is no real estate associated with the club. Our members live throughout Naples, including Pelican Bay, Park Shore, Gulf Shore Blvd, Old Naples and elsewhere.
The Club features - About Us Landing
The Club features a Bill Diddel designed golf course that was rebuilt and restored in 2009 by Gordon Lewis, and again in 2023 by Drew Rogers.   Whether you like to walk or take a golf cart, our membership offers you optimal playing conditions with the ability to walk the course all day, every day!

Contact & Directions
The Country Club of Naples
185 Burning Tree Dr.
Naples, FL 34105-6308
Phone:
(239) 261-1032
Email:
[email protected]
Employment Opportunities:
[email protected]
Convenient and centrally located
We are located one block off Goodlette Road between Pine Ridge and Solana Road.
Our neighbors are Moorings Park and Royal Poinciana Golf Club.
From north Naples: - Contact & Directions
From north Naples:
Take Goodlette Road south, and cross over Pine Ridge Road. Turn left at the second traffic light, Solana Road. Solana Road will turn into Burning Tree Drive as the road curves to the left. Follow Burning Tree until you come to the clubhouse.
From south Naples:
Take Goodlette Road to Solana Road. Turn right. Solana Road will turn into Burning Tree Drive as the road curves to the left. Follow Burning Tree until you come to the clubhouse.
From Park Shore and Gulf Shore Blvd:
Take 41 to Solana Road (DeVoe Cadillac is on the corner.) Solana will cross over Goodlette and becomes Burning Tree Drive as the road curves to the left. Follow Burning Tree Drive to the Club.
From I-75:
Take the Pine Ridge Road exit. Follow Pine Ridge Road to Goodlette Road and turn left. Turn left at the second traffic light, Solana Road. Solana Road will turn into Burning Tree Drive as the road curves to the left. Follow Burning Tree until you come to the clubhouse.
